08/12/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Top political and military leaders urged the EU Tuesday (7 December) to set a date for launching accession talks with Ankara. 
The National Security Council wants negotiations started without delay. 
Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan and Deniz Baykal, leader of the main opposition party CHP, issued a joint statement following talks Tuesday, reiterating that there is no alternative to full EU membership. 
Union leaders are to meet on 17 December to decide whether Ankara has met the necessary criteria. 
(FT - 08/12/04; AFP, NTV - 07/12/04)
